Defence drone targeting is a big mess.

The targetLocation field is set by DefenseDrone::SetWeaponTarget. This
determines whether the drone has a valid target or not.

In DefenseDrone::PickTarget, this is then immediately set back to the
invalid values of 0x7ffffff for x and y unless the target location
X and Y values are both in the range (-150, 450). This is what prevents
defence drones from defending the front of your ship.
